intensified 
friends allies and sympathizers of pretoria must be told 
clearly that the commonwealth will not allow this call to be 
suppressed by anyone until south africa is ready to dismantle her 
evil system said mugabe who also is current chairman of the 
101nation nonaligned movement 
he was opening a threeday meeting of the commonwealth committee 
seeking ways to increase external pressure on south africas 
government and bolster blackgoverned neighbors threatened by south 
african destabilization 
several of south africas neighbors are members of the 48member 
commonwealth a loose association of britain and its former 
colonies britain is not a member of the committee because prime 
minister margaret thatcher opposes sanctions 
mugabe applauded the usbrokered peace plan plotting 
independence for namibia also known as southwest africa after 
unsponsored elections in november 
but he said african nations remain deeply suspicious of south 
africas part in the agreement which angola and cuba also signed 
and fear attempts to weaken the un role in the territory pretoria 
has administered since world war 1 
