stoddard says the high cost of developing the land more than 
500000 an acre necessitated public financing 
theres no private developer in the world thats going to do 
that he says the only way that can be done is with substantial 
subsidy 
stoddard is convinced such ventures are necessary for areas like 
pittsburgh and the mon valley to prosper into the next century 
theres a sense of urgency on everyones part that we have to 
get started with this economic transformation and prepare for the 
next century he says we cant look back 
